			<p>But what Quokkas are most known for, is the fact that they look like they're smiling and their penchant for selfies. Quokkas have a happy, genial expression which is actually due to evolution. Like canines, Quokkas' mouths open slightly to pant allowing them to cool themselves. When they're happy and hot (which is quite often, especially this last few months), they seem like they are smiling.</p>
			<img src="/img/quokka_2.jpg" alt="" />
			<p>Although tourists and visitors to the island love Quokkas, the locals don't appreciate them as much. Due to their lack of fear for humans, Quokkas will regularly enter buildings such as homes or restaurants.</p>
